commit.message: Respect strict comparison when inside a nested comparison

Prepare for 8.1.0 release
zoneinfo module only arrived in Python 3.9
Unused imports

Implement strict comparison for datetime and time

These take fold into account, which their native equality checking fails to do.

Repare for 8.0.0 release
Allow an alternative separator to be used for traversal during replacement
Better error message when traversal fails
General tidy up of mocking docs

Allow string class attributes to be replaced
Fix ReST typo
Add TempDirectory option to manage current working directory

General TempDirectory documentation improvements

I'm not even sure people know what svn is anymore!
Use system default encoding where possible in TempDirectory
Allow TempDirectory instances to be traverses  as Path objects
Clean up testfixtures.sybil.FileParser API docs
Drop support for py.path.local
Don't look for Sybil examples in unit test source file
Introduce PY_312_PLUS compatibility constant
Remove explicit object bases
Rewrite Sybil integration for version 6 of Sybil
